   - Questionnaires: These are the most common method used to assess sexual orientation. Questionnaires like the Kinsey Scale, the Heterosexual-Homosexual Continuum, and the Sexual Orientation Identity Scale (SOIS) are widely used to measure the extent to which an individual identifies with heterosexual, homosexual, or bisexual orientations.
